# Docs Sync Required

- Documentation is part of the implementation, not a follow-up task.
- When scaffold output changes (templates, wizard options, default game, CLI messages), update `packages/kit/content/`
  (`AGENTS.md`, `docs/*.md`) and template READMEs in the same change when user-facing behavior shifts.
- When `bootstrap()` usage, starter game code, or public `BT` API names in generated games change, review kit
  `content/docs/basics.md`, `drawing.md`, `input.md`, and `palette.md` for stale examples.
- When the pinned engine range in `packages/create-blit-tech/src/scaffold.ts` (`BLIT_TECH_RANGE`) changes, note it in
  commit/PR text and check whether sibling repo `blit-tech` onboarding docs need a matching mention.
- When `pnpm run` scripts or preflight steps change, update `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md` and any affected
  `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` cross-references.
- Update root `README.md` or `CLAUDE.md` when commands, package layout, or wizard flow changes.
- When the `blit` CLI, agent adapters (`packages/kit/src/adapters.ts`), or `blit agents sync`
  (`packages/kit/src/commands/agents.ts`) change, update `packages/kit/README.md`,
  `packages/create-blit-tech/README.md`, and the design doc (`CREATE_BLIT_TECH_DESIGN.md`).
- When blit-tech public API changes in the sibling engine repo, audit kit `content/docs/` and the kit rule sources
  `packages/kit/content/rules/blit-api-names.md` and `blit-integer-coords.md` for stale names (`isDown`,
  `isOverlayEnabled`, etc.).
- If no docs update is needed, state why explicitly in the final response.
